<HEAD>

<TITLE>INIS at a Glance - Membership</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Stanik Zsolt">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="glance.htm"><IMG SRC="../graphic/glance.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
 <FONT SIZE=6>INIS Membership</FONT> <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
To join INIS, a formal request is made by the appropriate authority
to the Director General of the IAEA expressing the wish to participate
in INIS and undertaking to supply input regularly to the System.
Every INIS Member is represented in the System by a Liaison Officer
officially appointed by the national authority, or the Executive
Head in the case of an international organization. Currently,
there are 96 countries and 17 international organizations participating
in INIS. Membership in INIS is open to states who are members
of the IAEA, to United Nations organizations and to other subject-oriented
international or intergovernmental organizations. Since 1969 there
has been a standing invitation to join INIS directed to all potential
members by the Director General of the IAEA. Click here for information
on <A HREF="../liaison/liaison.htm">countries</A> and <A HREF="../liaison/liaison1.htm">organizations</A>
who belong to INIS and for <A HREF="../wwwlinks/other.htm">related</A>
Home Pages by country.
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT  SIZE=4><B>PRIVILEGES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</FONT></B>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
The rights, privileges, and responsibilities of INIS Members are
clearly defined by the IAEA Board of Governors in GOV/INF/743.
Rights include, for example, the ability to disseminate information
derived from all INIS products and services within their national
boundaries and the right to participate in Consultative Meetings
of INIS Liaison Officers. Privileges involve access to the INIS
Database, training, etc. INIS Member's responsibilities include
the selection of relevant literature published within a country's
national boundaries (or organizational confines, if an international
body) and the preparation of input and submission to the <A HREF="glansec.htm">INIS Secretariat</A>
, providing INIS information services, carrying out promotional
activities, etc. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG src="../graphic/toolbar.gif" usemap="#toolbar" BORDER=0 VSPACE=5>
<MAP name="toolbar"><AREA shape="rect" coords="1,1,125,46" href="../glance/glance.htm"><AREA shape="rect" coords="127,1,245,45" href="../whatsnew/whatsnew.htm"><AREA shape="rect" coords="247,1,365,46" href="../products/products.htm"><AREA shape="rect" coords="368,1,505,46" href="../wwwlinks/links.htm"><AREA shape="default" nohref></MAP></CENTER><CENTER>
<IMG src="../graphic/funcbar.gif" usemap="#funcbar" BORDER=0>
