<HEAD>

<TITLE>INIS at a Glance - Cooperation </TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Laura Roberson">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="glance.htm"><IMG SRC="../graphic/glance.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE=6>Co-operation</FONT> <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<FONT  SIZE=4><B>WITH THE ENERGY TECHNOLOGY DATA EXCHANGE</FONT>
</B>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
The Energy Technology Data Exchange (ETDE), a program of the International
Energy Agency (IEA), is a worldwide consortium of countries that
share energy-related scientific and technical information through
the Energy Database. The Exchange, as does INIS, recognizes the
benefits of collaboration and co-operation. A significant partnering
venture is with the International Atomic Energy Agency's International
Nuclear Information System (INIS). During the 15th ETDE Executive
Committee meeting in Cernay-la-Ville, France, in May 1994, the
two organizations formalized a longstanding relationship by signing
a Memorandum of Understanding (MOU). INIS and ETDE are both international
information systems that were established to facilitate information
sharing among their member countries. INIS focuses on the peaceful
uses of nuclear energy and environmental aspects of all energy;
ETDE focuses on all aspects of energy. All ETDE member countries
are also members of INIS. Because of this membership duality for
ETDE countries, the Exchange adopted INIS standards for information
exchange, with some minor modifications to accommodate ETDE's
broader scope. The agreement signed in 1994 identifies specific
areas for future co-operation, with a special emphasis on database
development and the assurance of data integrity. Goals for technical
cooperation include shared authorities, standards and publications.
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
As a result of the MOU, the ETDE Operating Agency for the first
time attended the INIS Liaison Officers meeting held in Vienna
in May 1995. That meeting also marked the celebration of INIS's
25th Anniversary. In October 1995, ETDE and INIS held the first
in a series of joint technical meetings which are expected to
lead to increased efficiency and cost-effectiveness for member
countries of both international information organizations. INIS
and ETDE continue to have joint technical meetings.<BR> For information
on the ETDE Database on CD-ROM, click <A HREF="../products/database/cd-rom.htm">here</A>
.<BR> For information on the ETDE Database online, click <A HREF="../products/database/online.htm">here</A>.
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<I>Links:</I> <A HREF="http://www.etde.org/">ETDE Home Page</A>
<BR>
<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG src="../graphic/toolbar.gif" usemap="#toolbar" BORDER=0 VSPACE=5>
