<HEAD>

<TITLE>INIS MICROFICHE of Non Conventional Literature</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Laura Roberson">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="../products.htm"><IMG SRC="../../graphic/prodserv.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER>
<BR>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE=6>INIS Microfiche of Non Conventional Literature</FONT>
<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<IMG SRC="../../graphic/1disk60.gif" WIDTH=250 HEIGHT=168 BORDER=0 ALIGN=right>
Literature reported to INIS may be subdivided into two categories,
conventional and non-conventional. Conventional literature is
that literature which is commercially available through the normal
distribution channels, such as the book and magazine trade or
publishing houses. Non-conventional literature comprises all other
forms of literature, including scientific and technical reports,
patent documents, pre-conference papers, and non-commercially
published theses not readily available through commercial channels.
Non-conventional literature is available through the INIS Clearinghouse.
The full text INIS collection comprises publications on peaceful
uses of nuclear energy from 1970 to the present. Publications
may be purchased without restriction. The legibility and quality
of microfiche depends on the technical quality of full size documents
received by the Clearinghouse. The quality of INIS microfiche
is above the international standard.<BR>
<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>INIS CLEARINGHOUSE</B> </FONT><BR>
<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<IMG SRC="../../graphic/1disk22.gif" WIDTH=249 HEIGHT=166 BORDER=0 ALIGN=left>
The INIS Clearinghouse, a unit within the INIS Secretariat of
the IAEA supplies, on request, microfiche copies of most of the
non-conventional literature announced in the INIS output products.
Microfiche copies are produced on photographic film in a standard
size of 105 mm x 148.75 mm. Each fiche can contain up to 98 pages
of original full text, reduced at a ratio of 24.1. The Report,
Standard and Patent Number Index of <A HREF="../database/atom.htm">INIS Atomindex</A>
serves as a catalog of full text documents available from the
INIS Clearinghouse.<BR>
<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>ORDERING OF INIS MICROFICHE<BR>
</B> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Microfiche copies of non-conventional literature may be ordered
by mail, fax or online. Payment can be made with mastercard, check,
bank transfer or by opening a deposit account with IAEA. Microfiche
could be ordered through the INIS <A HREF="mailto:chouse@nepo1.iaea.or.at">Clearinghouse</A>.
Online ordering of INIS microfiche may be done while browsing
the INIS Database on the IAEA host by INIS Members. Requests for
registration to use the INIS Database on the IAEA host should
be addressed to: <A HREF="mailto:flory@nepo1.iaea.or.at">flory@nepo1.iaea.or.at</A>
<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>Types of Orders and Costs</FONT><BR>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=3 WIDTH=530><B> <TR><TD ALIGN=left><FONT SIZE=3></B></B>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P>
<I>Annual Standing Order</I> (full collection)</FONT></TD><TD ALIGN=left><FONT SIZE=3>ATS
7.85/fiche</FONT></TD></TR> <TR><TD ALIGN=left><FONT SIZE=3><I>
Annual Standing Order<BR>
</I>(by prefix or by INIS Subject Category)</FONT></TD><TD ALIGN=left><FONT SIZE=3>ATS
58.00/document</FONT></TD></TR> <TR><TD ALIGN=left><FONT SIZE=3><I>Ad
hoc Order</I> (individual request) </FONT></TD><TD ALIGN=left>ATS
100.00/document (50% discount for developing countries)</TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN=left><FONT SIZE=3><I> Special Order<BR>
</I>(usually having a specific condition or theme) </FONT></TD><TD ALIGN=left><FONT SIZE=3>Cost
based on production</FONT></TD></TR> <TR><TD ALIGN=left><FONT SIZE=3><I>Floppy
Diskette </FONT></TD><TD ALIGN=left><FONT SIZE=3>Free with Standing
