<HEAD>

<TITLE>TRAINING</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Laura Roberson">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="../products.htm"><IMG SRC="../../graphic/prodserv.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER>
<BR>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE=6>TRAINING</FONT> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
It is very important for the quality of INIS output products
to ensure a common understanding of the INIS standards and rules
by the staff of all inputting centers of INIS Members. For this
reason, the INIS Training Program plays a significant role in
INIS activity. All aspects of INIS operations are thoroughly considered
in the training events organized by the IAEA for INIS members,
including selection criteria, abstracting, descriptive cataloging,
indexing, retrieval, marketing and promotion. The training events
are aimed at assisting INIS Members in training personnel newly
involved in input preparation and utilization of output products.
A PC-Based Training Package is under development for individual
training. Through the IAEA program of Technical Co-operation,
the INIS Secretariat provides assistance to developing countries
participating in INIS in their establishment and operatio of information
systems on nuclear energy. The Technical Co-operation Program
includes Group Fellowship Training, Regional Training and Fellowships
and Scientific Visits.<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>1. TRAINING PROGRAM OBJECTIVES</B> <BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
The INIS Training Program is designed to meet a number of objectives:</FONT> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
- Establishment and improvement of a national information infrastructure</FONT>
<BR>
- Transfer of modern information technology</FONT> <BR>
- Fostering exchange of scientific and technical information</FONT>
<BR>
- High quality and coverage of the INIS Database</FONT> <BR>
- Maximum utilization of INIS output products</FONT> <BR>
- Responsiveness to country needs <BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>2. INIS TRAINING SEMINARS</B> <BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=80%><TR><TD VALIGN=top>INIS Training Seminars
are generally held on &quot;even&quot; years usually in Vienna.
The seminars are funded and staffed by INIS and emphasize INIS
input skills and use of INIS output products.</TD><TD><IMG SRC="../../graphic/1disk28.gif" WIDTH=249 HEIGHT=167 BORDER=0 ALIGN=></TD></TR></TABLE>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>3. PC-BASED TRAINING PACKAGE</B> <BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
A PC-Based Training Package designed for individualized study
and training is currently under development. The package will
contain a general introduction to INIS, a Bibliographic Description
module and a Subject Analysis module. It will be available to
INIS Members on CD-ROM in late 1996.<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>4. TECHNICAL CO-OPERATION TRAINING</B> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
INIS works in conjunction with the IAEA Technical Co-operation
Department to organize Group Fellowship and Regional Training
for Member States. Individual training in the form of Fellowships
and Scientific Visits are also organized jointly by INIS and Technical
Co-operation.
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>GROUP FELLOWSHIP TRAINING</B> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Group Fellowship Training is sponsored by the IAEA Technical Co-operation
organization in conjunction with INIS. It is designed to meet
individual country needs. It is generally hosted by a Member State
during &quot;odd&quot; years, has a three to five weeks duration
and the instructors include both INIS staff and host country staff.
<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>REGIONAL TRAINING</B> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Regional Training is sponsored by the IAEA Technical Co-operation
organization in conjunction with INIS. It is generally related
to Technical Co-operation Projects and is hosted by a Member State
in the Region. The length of the training varies and the instructors
may be INIS and/or host country staff.<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>FELLOWSHIPS AND SCIENTIFIC VISITS<BR>
</B> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Fellowships and scientific visits are sponsored by the IAEA Technical
Co-operation organization in conjunction with INIS. A Fellowship
is designed for junior staff members in Member States, generally
has a two to three month duration in a single geographic area,
and constitutes on-the-job training. A Scientific Visit on the
other hand, is designed for senior staff in a Member State and
has a duration of from one to three weeks in more than one location.
<BR>
<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG src="../../graphic/toolbar.gif" usemap="#toolbar" BORDER=0 VSPACE=5>
