<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>Full-Text Electronic Documents</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Stanik Zsolt">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="../products.htm"><IMG SRC="../../graphic/prodserv.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER>
<BR>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE=6>Full-Text Electronic Documents</FONT> <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
A distinctive feature of the INIS system is that it collects,
maintains and provides availability to an archival collection
of internationally generated documents. <BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman">Full text of original documents that
are not available through the usual commercial channels, namely
<I>non-conventional literature</I> such as research reports, patents,
conference papers, theses, laws, regulations and standards, etc.
can be ordered as <A HREF="../microfic/index.htm">INIS Microfiche</A>.
<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
The languages of all referenced original (full text) publications
are English 76%; Russian 8%; German 5%; Japanese 3%; French 2%;
Portuguese 1%; and others 5%. <BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<I>Links:</I> <A HREF="index1.htm">Index to full text electronic documents available on the INIS Home Page</A>
.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

