<HEAD>

<TITLE>Electronic Information Exchange</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Anatoli Tolstenkov">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="../products.htm"><IMG SRC="../../graphic/prodserv.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER>
<BR>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE=6>Electronic Information Exchange</FONT> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
The INIS Liaison Officers were informed in 1996 of INIS Atomindex files and other information so far available from the
INIS Section via FTP. The address of the IAEA  FTP Server is:  <b>"nesihp04.iaea.or.at"</b>. Access to the INIS directory is password protected.
<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>List of INIS Output Products and other Information available via FTP:
<BR>
</B> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
There is one main directory and three subdirectories that
contain information for the INIS user:<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<b>/ -</b>  INIS Atomindex and Authority files<BR>
<b>/reference -</b> INIS Reference Series<B> </B>manuals <BR>
<b>/mfhead -</b> Microfiche header information<br>
<b>/tools</b> - UNIX and DOS tools 
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
The following is not a complete list but serves to draw attention
to particular files.
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
In the <B>/ </B> (main) directory you will find these files:
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<p>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<ul>
<li><b>atVVSSII.zip</b> - 
Atomindex file with two issues SS and II of volume VV
<br>
<li><b>atmfVVSS.zip</b> - Atomindex file with issue SS and II of volume VV<br>
<li><b>ccVVSS.zip</b> - INIS corporate authority (with country codes) which corresponds to volume VV issue SS of Atomindex file<br>
<li><b>cnVVSS.zip</b> - INIS corporate authority (with country names) which corresponds to volume VV issue SS of Atomindex file<br>
<li><b>jallVVSS.zip</b> - INIS journal authority (longer version) which corresponds to volume VV issue SS of Atomindex file<br>
<li><b>jtilVVSS.zip</b> - INIS journal authority (shorter version) which corresponds to volume VV issue SS of Atomindex file<br>
<li><b>thes.zip</b> -  file with the latest version of INIS Thesaurus<br>
<li><b>thes.trm</b> -  INIS Thesaurus file format description<br>
</ul>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
In the <B>/reference</B> subdirectory you will find files:<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<ul>
<li><b>inis.zip</b> -  IAEA-INIS-1 <b> INIS: Guide to Bibliographic Description</b> (WordPerfect)<br> 
<li><b>inis7.zip</b> - IAEA-INIS-7 <b>INIS: Specifications for Machine-readable Data
Exchange</b> (Word 6.0)<br> 
<li><b>inis12.zip</b> -  IAEA-INIS-12 <b>INIS:
Manual for Subject Analysis</b> (WordPerfect)<br>
<li><b>inis21.zip</b> -  IAEA-INIS-21<b> INIS: Guidelines for Standardized Entry
of Corporate Bodies</b> (WordPerfect)<br>
<li><b>inis23.zip</b> -  IAEA-INIS-23:<b> INIS: FIBRE User's Manual</b> (Word 6.0)<br>
</ul>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P>
