<p><b><i>Note:</i></b> The total includes the following data in Taiwan,China:
</p>

<p>6 unit(s), 4884 MW(e) in operation; 33.93 TW(e).h of nuclear electricity
generation, representing 28.79% of the total electricity generated there;
86 year(s) 1 month(s) of total operating experience. 
<br>2 Shutdowns in 1995: Bruce 2 in Canada but it can re-start in future,
Wuergassen in Germany.</p>

<p><b>Connection to the grid during 1995</b> </p>

<ul>
<p>India IN-10, Kakrapar-2 PHWR 
<br>Korea RP KR-12, Yonggwang-4 PWR 
<br>UK GB-24, Sizewell-B PWR 
<br>Ukraine UA-127, Zaporozhe-6 WWER 
<br></p>
</ul>

<p><i><b>Note:</b> Japan reported that Onagawa 2 and Monju NPP were connected
to the grid in 1994</i> 
