<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Bio-data of E. Gail de Planque
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<IMG SRC="/worldatom/images/deplanq.jpg" align=left>
<H3><I>E. Gail de Planque</I></H3>
<P>
<B><I>Committee Chairwoman</I></B>
<P>
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<I>Dr. de Planque is a radiation specialist and a former Commissioner of the United States Nuclear Regulatory Commission.
She holds an A.B. degree in mathematics form
Immaculata College, an M.S. degree in physics from New Jersey
Institute of Technology, and a Ph.D. in environmental health
sciences from New York University.
<P>
As a researcher, Dr. de Planque has published over 60 articles
and reports in the field of radiation protection and
dosimetry.  She pioneered the application of
thermoluminescence dosimeters in environmental monitoring,
organizing and conducting a series of international
intercomparisons for these devices.  She has chaired and
served on working groups for such organizations as the
American National Standards Institute, the International
Organization for Standardization and the International
Electrotechnical Commission and has been on the scientific and
editorial committees of the recent International Conferences
on Solid State Dosimetry.
<P>
Dr. de Planque is a Fellow of the American Nuclear Society,
serving as its President for 1988-89.  She is also a member of
the Board of Directors and the National Executive Committee of
this organization.  She is a member of the Health Physics
Society, serves as an Adjunct Research Professor at the New
York University Medical Center, and is on the editorial board
of the journal 'Radiation Protection Dosimetry'.</I>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR SIZE=1 NOSHADE>
</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
